title: George Clooney, Amal Clooney pregnant with twins: report | Daily Telegraph

organizations.name: sixth world congress of pontifical foundation scholas

text:
AMAL and George Clooney are reportedly expecting twins.
It has long been speculated that the power couple — who were married in September 2014 — is pregnant.
The twins are said to be due in June though hugely successful human rights lawyer Amal, 39, and Ocean’s Eleven actor George, 55, are yet to release an official statement.
Well-connected Hollywood source Julie Chen made the claim on her American TV show, The Talk .
“Beyoncé is not the only superstar expecting twins,” Chen said, nypost.com reports.
media_camera Amal and George Clooney, pictured attending a meeting of Pope Francis with the participants of the Sixth World Congress of Pontifical Foundation Scholas, in the Vatican. Picture: AFP
“Congratulations are in order for George and Amal Clooney,” she said, according to Us Weekly .
“What we did find out is that the twins are due this June.”
This is How Amal Clooney has changed George Clooney for the better 1:00 George says, since getting married back in September 2014, Quote: 'I've never been happier in a relationship by any stretch of the imagination. At 52, I found the love of my life and I'm really happy!'
May 13th 2016 9 months ago /video/video.news.com.au/Entertainment/Celebrity/ This is How Amal Clooney has changed George Clooney for the better Reports last month suggested Amal was pregnant after she was photographed with what was speculated to be a growing baby bump.
Rumours of Amal’s pregnancy began when a family friend revealed the news to Lebanon’s Daily Star in January. At the time, InTouch magazine suggested Amal was having a boy and a girl.
media_camera Amal and George Clooney are starting a family, a friend has confirmed. Picture: AFP Originally published as George and Amal are ‘expecting twins’
